From: Kyle Camera Local Quirk <kyle@example.invalid>
Subject: [PATCH] pipewire-v4l2: expose YUYV through ffmpeg conversion

The IPU7/OV08X40 camera reaches PipeWire through libcamera as RGB-only
formats. Browsers can consume that through the PipeWire camera path, but Zoom
only sees the camera through the legacy V4L2 shim and fails to render the
stock pw-v4l2 AR24/XR24 stream. Advertise YUYV as a compatibility format,
prefer it when legacy clients ask for defaults, default that path to 1080p,
advertise a 30 fps frame interval for HD modes, force PipeWire's ffmpeg video
converter for that format, and map buffers so legacy mmap V4L2 clients can
dequeue converted YUYV frames.

--- a/pipewire-v4l2/src/pipewire-v4l2.c
+++ b/pipewire-v4l2/src/pipewire-v4l2.c
